Help on Hiragana from youtube video...
by penholdr » Tue 07.14.2009 12:49 am So this phrase has been bothering me for the longest time, my japanese ear must not be all that good. The video is a clip from an episode of Sailor Moon. at 5 minutes and 30 seconds into the video, in response to "please go back and be seated." a girl says, "no way"... or atleast that's how it's translated. but i've been trying to figure out the hiragana for her "no way" for the longest time.i think it sounds like:そう わけない はsou wakenai waor sou aikenai wasomething like that, however I can't figure out if those phrases really make sense at all in context. From this youtube video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oeTVIQgFn2Uif anyone could help me figure this out that would be awesome!thanks!
penholdr
Posts: 2Joined: Tue 07.14.2009 12:34 am
